Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION congratulating the
2 Hamilton Southeastern High School girls soccer team on
3 winning the 2025 Indiana High School Athletic Association
4 (IHSAA) Class 3A state championship.
5 Whereas, On Saturday, November 1, 2025, the Hamilton
6 Southeastern (HSE) High School girls soccer team, the Royals,
7 defeated Carmel High School 1-0 for the IHSAA Class 3A girls
8 soccer state championship;
9 Whereas, HSE finished the 2025-2026 season with a 22-0-1
10 record, their only draw coming against Zionsville on September
11 24;
12 Whereas, Led by Head Coach Greg Davidson, with the
13 assistance of Alyssa Minnick and Mallory Rondeau, the Royals
14 only conceded six goals over the 2025 season, while scoring
15 one hundred and four goals;
16 Whereas, During the championship game, senior forward
17 Riley Boyd scored with less than six minutes remaining and
18 goalkeeper Hannah Dodge had five saves;
19 Whereas, Boyd, along with fellow senior Sloane May, led
20 the team with 15 goals each during the season;
21 Whereas, Senior defender Blair Satterfield was named the
22 Mental Attitude Award winner for Class 3A girls soccer; and
23 Whereas, The HSE Royals' dominant season concluded
2026 RC 1522/DI JR

2
1 with their first time winning the state championship title:
2 Therefore,
3 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
4 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
5 concurring:
6 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly
7 congratulates the Hamilton Southeastern High School girls
8 soccer team on winning their first IHSAA state championship.
9 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
10 to transmit copies of this Resolution to Riley Boyd, Brooklyn
11 Boyle, Rylie Brydges, Sydney Cook, Hannah Dodge, Nicole
12 Donato, Grace Gerstner, Kinsley Good, Raegan Hahaj,
13 Margaux Henning, Lauren Kutoloski, Sloane May, Sydney
14 May, Addison McClain, Olivia Moore, Kate Noel, Lillian
15 Palmer, Kherington Patton, Rileigh Pierce, Sophia Reising,
16 Kaylee Reitmeier, Jenneva Rogers, Bailey Sapp, Blair
17 Satterfield, Izzie Springer, Rebekah TeKrony, and coach Greg
18 Davidson.
2026 RC 1522/DI JR

